[2
Date: 1 Apr 2000 10:58:47 -0500 (EST)
From: Dr. Norman Ronald <n-ronald@TVMDL.TAMU.EDU>

The Associate Infectious and Parasitic Disease Knowledge base suggests a
differential of Hantavirus infection, meningococcal infection and
_Legionella_ infection for the diseases known to occur in Saudi Arabia. We
have insufficient data on another disease caused by Fakeev Virus (Saudi
Mystery Disease), therefore we can not rule this disease in or out.
--
N.C. Ronald Ph.D.
Editor IPD
TVMDL-TAMU
